@NODE Briefly "Briefly"

                @{b}Briefly@{ub}


    This is a collection of Anims and Buttons for ReqAttack in the style of your favourite
icon collection, plus a few other bits I thought might be useful. 

    (Brief enough?)


    < @{" Front Page   " LINK Main}
    > @{" Introduction " LINK Introduction}
@ENDNODE

@NODE Introduction "Introduction"

                @{b}Introduction to Fuzzy GlowAttack@{ub}


    If you don't like reading long inrtoductions try this one @{" Not so detailed Intro " LINK ShortIntro}

    Well firsty I want to thank you for looking at this pack as it's my first attempt at
supplying the Amiga community with any form of software at all, so please forgive me if
things seem a bit simple.

    Back in the olden days a program called 'Arq' was given to the Amiga world that provided
us something we hadn't seen before, animated requester things. "That's nice", I thought "But
I want to make my own animations for it". I waited and waited.... Then waited a bit more. As
my Amiga grew older, got kitted out with new clothes and began to look more tarty, this
wonderful program started to look a bit out dated. So eventually off it went. Then there was
'MRQ', that looked nicer but just kept on crashing my system so I just got rid of that one.

    Enter ReqAttack.... Now that's more like it.

    This, as you may have gathered by the REALLY brief @{" Brief " LINK Briefly} page (Yes twice), this is
a collection of Buttons and Anims for ReqAttack v1.80+. You will need v1.80+ due to the
"Child" feature (It'll make sense if you use it).

    Over the months I have gathered up tons (In bytes) of Glow icons and many other forms
of Glow type images and a few weeks ago decided, since I hadn't seen any "Glows" for the
ReqAttack package, to get a set of Anims on the go.

    Then, only a few days after decided to do this, a set of "MI" Anims arrived on the AmiNet.
Typical I thought, so I downloaded the archive to have a look and to my surprise it wasn't
as adventurous as I first presumed it would -or could- be. There was just a few Anims that
couldn't possibly cover the many requesters that are thrown our way in every day (And not
so everyay) use, and I hate having 'part' one thing an 'part' another. So back I went to
continue building this pack out of the building blocks I had acquired. Ooh, while I remember,
will you let me know if there are any spelling mistakes that slip through the net? Cheers.

    Now you might be thinking, "Oh, he's just got a load of Glow icons and converted them
info RAAnims (ReqAttack Anims for those that don't know). Well to start with I did. But
then things started to get a bit out of hand. Instead of simply having a 2 frame anim which
consisted of "No glow, Glow, No Glow, Glow..." I changed them to all no Glow.... Then PART
of the image to Glow again (The bit that seemed important to the Anim/Requester), these
looked nice, so I kept them. This package is basically some of my 2 frame anims, now don't
go off thinking "Boring". They look nice and my multi frame ones are on the go but they take
ages as I work full time and work most nights too.

    Finally, In this package there are 2 types of anims, with and without borders. I use the
ones without borders but you might prefer the borders. I need you lot out there in the world
to tell me which ones you use because when I (eventually) upload more 2 frame anims and the
multi frame anims the archive will get bigger and I would like to drop the bordered anims
but that's up to you.

    Enjoy.


    < @{" Front Page   " LINK Main}
    > @{" Requirements " LINK Requirements}
@ENDNODE

